{
  "id": "guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors",
  "title": "avoid-combining-selectors",
  "contents": "\n\n\n  <div class=\"github-links\">\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/master/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\" aria-label=\"Suggest Edits\" title=\"Suggest Edits\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">mode_edit</i></a>\n  </div>\n\n\n<div class=\"content\">\n<h1 id=\"avoid-combining-selectors\">avoid-combining-selectors<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#avoid-combining-selectors\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n<p>Prefer combining selectors at the selector level.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Type</strong>: suggestion</li>\n<li><strong>Recommended</strong>: Yes</li>\n<li><strong>Fixable</strong>: No</li>\n<li><strong>Suggestion</strong>: No</li>\n<li><strong>Requires type checking</strong>: No</li>\n<li><strong>Configurable</strong>: No</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- Everything above this generated, do not edit -->\n<!-- MANUAL-DOC:START -->\n<h2 id=\"rule-details\">Rule Details<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#rule-details\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>A selector is a pure function that is used to derive state.\nBecause a selector is a pure function (and a synchronous function), it's easier to test.</p>\n<p>That's why it's recommended to build a view model by composing multiple selectors into one selector, instead of consuming multiple selector observable streams to create a view model in the component.</p>\n<p>Examples of <strong>incorrect</strong> code for this rule:</p>\n<h3 id=\"enrich-state-with-other-state-in-component\">Enrich state with other state in component<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#enrich-state-with-other-state-in-component\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h3>\n<code-example language=\"ts\">\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#export\" class=\"code-anchor\">export</a> class Component {\n  vm$ = combineLatest(\n    this.store.select(selectCustomers),\n    this.store.select(selectOrders)\n  ).pipe(\n    map(([customers, orders]) => {\n      return customers.map((c) => {\n        return {\n          customerId: c.id,\n          name: c.name,\n          orders: orders.filter((o) => o.customerId === c.id),\n        };\n      });\n    })\n  );\n}\n</code-example>\n<h3 id=\"filter-state-in-component\">Filter state in component<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#filter-state-in-component\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h3>\n<code-example language=\"ts\">\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#export\" class=\"code-anchor\">export</a> class Component {\n  customer$ = this.store\n    .select(selectCustomers)\n    .pipe(withLatestFrom(this.store.select(selectActiveCustomerId)))\n    .pipe(\n      map(([customers, customerId]) => {\n        return customers[customerId];\n      })\n    );\n}\n</code-example>\n<p>Examples of <strong>correct</strong> code for this rule:</p>\n<h3 id=\"enrich-state-with-other-state-in-selector\">Enrich state with other state in selector<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#enrich-state-with-other-state-in-selector\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h3>\n<code-example language=\"ts\">\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#export\" class=\"code-anchor\">export</a> selectCustomersAndOrders = <a href=\"api/store/createSelector\" class=\"code-anchor\">createSelector</a>(\n  selectCustomers,\n  selectOrders,\n  (customers, orders) => {\n    return {\n      customerId: c.id,\n      name: c.name,\n      orders: orders.filter((o) => o.customerId === c.id),\n    }\n  }\n)\n\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#export\" class=\"code-anchor\">export</a> class Component {\n  vm$ = this.store.select(selectCustomersAndOrders);\n}\n</code-example>\n<h3 id=\"filter-state-in-selector\">Filter state in selector<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#filter-state-in-selector\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h3>\n<code-example language=\"ts\">\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#export\" class=\"code-anchor\">export</a> selectActiveCustomer = <a href=\"api/store/createSelector\" class=\"code-anchor\">createSelector</a>(\n  selectCustomers,\n  selectActiveCustomerId,\n  ([customers, customerId]) => {\n    return customers[customerId];\n  }\n)\n\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#export\" class=\"code-anchor\">export</a> class Component {\n  customer$ = this.store.select(selectActiveCustomer);\n}\n</code-example>\n<h2 id=\"further-reading\">Further reading<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#further-reading\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://brandonroberts.dev/blog/posts/2020-12-14-maximizing-simplifying-component-views-ngrx-selectors/#building-view-models\">Maximizing and Simplifying Component Views with NgRx Selectors - by Brandon Roberts</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n</div>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#export\n - api/store/createSelector\n - guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#avoid-combining-selectors\n - guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#enrich-state-with-other-state-in-component\n - guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#enrich-state-with-other-state-in-selector\n - guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#filter-state-in-component\n - guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#filter-state-in-selector\n - guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#further-reading\n - guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors#rule-details\n - https://brandonroberts.dev/blog/posts/2020-12-14-maximizing-simplifying-component-views-ngrx-selectors/#building-view-models\n - https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/master/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/eslint-plugin/rules/avoid-combining-selectors.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\n-->"
